signatures.text: operator fun <K, V> MutableMap<K, V>.minusAssign(key: K)
signatures.desc: Removes the entry with the given key from this mutable map.

signatures.text: operator fun <K, V> MutableMap<K, V>.minusAssign( keys: Iterable<K>)
signatures.desc: Removes all entries the keys of which are contained in the given keys collection from this mutable map.

signatures.text: operator fun <K, V> MutableMap<K, V>.minusAssign( keys: Array<out K>)
signatures.desc: Removes all entries the keys of which are contained in the given keys array from this mutable map.

signatures.text: operator fun <K, V> MutableMap<K, V>.minusAssign( keys: Sequence<K>)
signatures.desc: Removes all entries from the keys of which are contained in the given keys sequence from this mutable map.

signatures.text: operator fun <T> MutableCollection<in T>.minusAssign( element: T)
signatures.desc: Removes a single instance of the specified element from this mutable collection.

signatures.text: operator fun <T> MutableCollection<in T>.minusAssign( elements: Iterable<T>)
signatures.desc: Removes all elements contained in the given elements collection from this mutable collection.

signatures.text: operator fun <T> MutableCollection<in T>.minusAssign( elements: Array<T>)
signatures.desc: Removes all elements contained in the given elements array from this mutable collection.

signatures.text: operator fun <T> MutableCollection<in T>.minusAssign( elements: Sequence<T>)
signatures.desc: Removes all elements contained in the given elements sequence from this mutable collection.
